<HL>
   Technology Brief -- Computer Sciences Corp.:
   Firm Plans Tender Offer
   To Acquire U.K. Concern
</HL>
<DATE>
05/14/91
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B5
</SO>
<CO>
   CSC U.BUT
</CO>
<MS>
TECHNOLOGY (TEC)
</MS>
<IN>
SOFTWARE (SOF)
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<NS>
ACQUISITIONS &amp; MERGERS, TAKEOVERS, BOARD BATTLES (TNM)
</NS>
<RE>
CALIFORNIA (CA)
GREAT BRITAIN (UK)
</RE>
<LP>
   Computer Sciences Corp. said it plans to acquire Butler
Cox PLC, a London information technology management
consulting firm, through a public tender offer valued at
about $22.5 million.
   Computer Sciences said it is offering to purchase all of
Butler Cox's shares for #2.45 ($4.22) a share. Butler Cox has
5,343,293 shares outstanding on the London Stock Exchange.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Computer Sciences, which supplies information technology
services to industry and governments, said Butler Cox has
annual revenue of $18 million. The tender offer will begin
within a few days and will last for at least 30 days, a
Computer Sciences spokesman said. The El Segundo, Calif.,
company said the acquisition would substantially expand its
European operations.
</TEXT>
